From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 18/20] jsonrpc: emit events when stockstrings change so
 language switch is seamless

set_stock_strings updated the shared stock translations but emitted no
events, so already-rendered, cached UI text that embeds stock strings
(chatlist message summaries, self/device contact names, connectivity
view) stayed in the old language until a full reload. This is the
"language switch doesn't refresh the UI" bug.

Add stock_str::emit_events_for_updated_stock_strings() and call it once
for the selected account after the stock strings are applied, emitting
ChatlistItemChanged, ContactsChanged(SELF/DEVICE) and ConnectivityChanged
so the UI refetches the affected data automatically.

Backport of chatmail/core#7719 by Simon Laux (closed unmerged) /
deltachat-desktop#5403, ported to the pinned core (the upstream import
hunk was de-duplicated and the call site adapted to this tree's
set_stock_strings).
---
 deltachat-jsonrpc/src/api.rs |  6 +++++-
 src/stock_str.rs             | 15 +++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 20 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/deltachat-jsonrpc/src/api.rs b/deltachat-jsonrpc/src/api.rs
index 3b3de507e..ab910004b 100644
--- a/deltachat-jsonrpc/src/api.rs
+++ b/deltachat-jsonrpc/src/api.rs
@@ -34,7 +34,7 @@
 use deltachat::qr_code_generator::{create_qr_svg, generate_backup_qr, get_securejoin_qr_svg};
 use deltachat::reaction::{get_msg_reactions, send_reaction};
 use deltachat::securejoin;
-use deltachat::stock_str::StockMessage;
+use deltachat::stock_str::{emit_events_for_updated_stock_strings, StockMessage};
 use deltachat::storage_usage::{get_blobdir_storage_usage, get_storage_usage};
 use deltachat::webxdc::StatusUpdateSerial;
 use deltachat::EventEmitter;
@@ -476,6 +476,10 @@ async fn set_stock_strings(&self, strings: HashMap<u32, String>) -> Result<()> {
                 accounts.set_stock_translation(stock_id, stock_message)?;
             }
         }
+        // In the existing clients only one account is visible at a time.
+        if let Some(context) = accounts.get_selected_account() {
+            emit_events_for_updated_stock_strings(&context);
+        }
         Ok(())
     }
 
diff --git a/src/stock_str.rs b/src/stock_str.rs
index 886f57b6b..75f87dbe8 100644
--- a/src/stock_str.rs
+++ b/src/stock_str.rs
@@ -1253,6 +1253,21 @@ pub(crate) async fn update_device_chats(&self) -> Result<()> {
     }
 }
 
+/// Emits events to invalidate cached data which contains core translated content
+///
+/// Only call this once after updating all your stockstrings,
+/// NOT after every single call to set_stock_translation, just once in the end.
+pub fn emit_events_for_updated_stock_strings(ctx: &Context) {
+    // update chatlist, which can contain all kinds of stockstrings in the message summary
+    ctx.emit_event(crate::EventType::ChatlistItemChanged { chat_id: None });
+    // And to update contact name [StockMessage::SelfMsg]
+    ctx.emit_event(crate::EventType::ContactsChanged(Some(ContactId::SELF)));
+    // To update bio/status [StockMessage::DeviceMessagesHint]
+    ctx.emit_event(crate::EventType::ContactsChanged(Some(ContactId::DEVICE)));
+    // reload connectivity view, which contains various stock stings
+    ctx.emit_event(crate::EventType::ConnectivityChanged);
+}
+
 impl Accounts {
     /// Set the stock string for the [StockMessage].
     ///
